# Error Prevention and Code Quality Guidelines
/* Usage: Apply these rules to prevent common errors and maintain code quality
   When to Use:
   - During active development
   - Code review processes
   - Debugging sessions
   - System architecture design
   - Performance optimization */

## Error Prevention Protocol

/* Validation & Safety Section */
// Apply these rules when:
// - Implementing new features
// - Handling user input
// - Managing system boundaries
// - Working with external services
// - Dealing with async operations
1. **Validation & Safety**
   - Implement comprehensive error boundaries
   - Validate all inputs at system boundaries
   - Handle all edge cases proactively
   - Implement proper type checking
   - Maintain strict null safety
   - Implement proper error logging
   - Use proper error recovery mechanisms
   - Implement circuit breakers
   - Maintain proper fallback mechanisms
   - Implement proper retry mechanisms
   - Handle all async operations safely
   - Implement proper memory management
   - Maintain proper resource cleanup
   - Handle browser compatibility issues
   - Implement proper security measures

/* Code Quality Section */
// Follow these rules when:
// - Writing new code
// - Refactoring existing code
// - Reviewing pull requests
// - Optimizing performance
// - Managing technical debt
2. **Avoidance Rules**
   - AVOID premature optimization
   - AVOID inconsistent naming
   - AVOID hardcoding values
   - AVOID duplicate code
   - AVOID direct DOM manipulation
   - AVOID mixing business logic with UI
   - AVOID unnecessary dependencies
   - AVOID global state when possible
   - AVOID nested callbacks
   - AVOID security vulnerabilities
   - AVOID tight coupling
   - AVOID magic numbers
   - AVOID complex inheritance
   - AVOID blocking main thread
   - AVOID memory leaks
